SIMPLE: stealing
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stealing
<hw>Steal"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of taking
feloniously the personal property of another without his consent and
knowledge; theft; larceny.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is stolen; stolen property; -- chiefly
used in the plural.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stealingly</ent>⟦br⟧
